From 𝐒𝐞𝐫𝐯𝐢𝐜𝐞 𝐛𝐚𝐬𝐞𝐝 𝐜𝐨𝐦𝐩𝐚𝐧𝐲 to Amazon Interview Experience!🙆🏼
𝐂𝐨𝐦𝐩𝐞𝐧𝐬𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧: Base 19.5 LPA , 6.5 L Sign on Bonus Year-1 + 5.18 Sign on bonus Year-2, RSU 15.56 L (Vested in 4 years)
𝐏𝐨𝐬𝐢𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧: SDE1
𝐂𝐨𝐥𝐥𝐞𝐠𝐞: Not from well known (Can’t disclose the name)
𝐏𝐫𝐢𝐨𝐫 𝐞𝐱𝐩𝐞𝐫𝐢𝐞𝐧𝐜𝐞: 2 yrs 3 months (Worked in Service based company, Can’t disclose name)
𝐀𝐩𝐩𝐥𝐢𝐞𝐝: HR directly reached out on Linkedin

𝐑𝐨𝐮𝐧𝐝-𝟏 𝐎𝐧𝐥𝐢𝐧𝐞 𝐀𝐬𝐬𝐞𝐬𝐬𝐦𝐞𝐧𝐭
DSA Q-1 A medium-level problem based on strings and sorting.
DSA Q-2 A hard-level problem based on graphs.
Other: Multiple-choice questions based on Amazon Leadership Principles.
𝐏𝐞𝐫𝐟𝐨𝐫𝐦𝐚𝐧𝐜𝐞:Candidate solved all 2 dsa questions and received an interview call.

𝐑𝐨𝐮𝐧𝐝-𝟐 𝐃𝐒𝐀 + 𝐋𝐞𝐚𝐝𝐞𝐫𝐬𝐡𝐢𝐩 (𝐁𝐞𝐡𝐚𝐯𝐢𝐨𝐫𝐚𝐥)
DSA Q-1 Rotten Orange (BFS + Matrix, medium)
Ref: https://lnkd.in/g6RBg_th
DSA Q-2 Binary Tree Maximum Path Sum (Dp + Tree, Hard)
Ref: https://lnkd.in/g2xSPCJq
𝐏𝐞𝐫𝐟𝐨𝐫𝐦𝐚𝐧𝐜𝐞: Candidate could complete all two questions with optimal TC. 
𝐅𝐞𝐞𝐝𝐛𝐚𝐜𝐤 𝐑𝐞𝐜𝐞𝐢𝐯𝐞𝐝: Coding questions were very good but mixed for the Amazon Leadership Principles. The candidate was advised to better prepare for the Leadership Principles questions in the upcoming rounds

𝐑𝐨𝐮𝐧𝐝-𝟑 𝐃𝐒𝐀 + 𝐋𝐞𝐚𝐝𝐞𝐫𝐬𝐡𝐢𝐩 (𝐁𝐞𝐡𝐚𝐯𝐢𝐨𝐫𝐚𝐥)
DSA Q-1 Walls and Gates (Grid Multi Source BFS, Medium)
Ref: https://lnkd.in/gKXJ978T
DSA Q-2 Group Anagrams (Hashing , Medium)
Ref: https://lnkd.in/gSZX3R2w 
Candidate was also asked 2-3 leadership questions. 
𝐏𝐞𝐫𝐟𝐨𝐫𝐦𝐚𝐧𝐜𝐞: Candidate could complete all two questions with optimal TC. 
𝐅𝐞𝐞𝐝𝐛𝐚𝐜𝐤 𝐑𝐞𝐜𝐞𝐢𝐯𝐞𝐝: The HR mentioned that the feedback was positive, and will move to the next round..

𝐑𝐨𝐮𝐧𝐝-𝟒 𝐃𝐒𝐀 + 𝐋𝐞𝐚𝐝𝐞𝐫𝐬𝐡𝐢𝐩 (𝐁𝐞𝐡𝐚𝐯𝐢𝐨𝐫𝐚𝐥)
DSA Q-1 Maximum Profit in Job Scheduling (Binary Search + DP, Hard)
Ref: https://lnkd.in/gNXiinWG 
Candidate was asked 4-5 leadership questions.
𝐏𝐞𝐫𝐟𝐨𝐫𝐦𝐚𝐧𝐜𝐞: Candidate could complete the dsa question in optimal TC. Candidate also answered all leadership questions using the STAR (Situation, Task, Action, Result) pattern relating his experience in a very good way.
𝐅𝐞𝐞𝐝𝐛𝐚𝐜𝐤 𝐑𝐞𝐜𝐞𝐢𝐯𝐞𝐝: Wait for the final results! Most impatient moments 😰😨

Candidate received an offer in Amazon. From Service based to #FAANG, now rest is history !🥳🥳

𝐍𝐨𝐭𝐞: DSA questions were pretty standard but were of medium-hard leetcode level. Leadership principles are very important to get into Amazon, don't neglect this.

Stay tuned for more such detailed interview experiences🙌.

